Thank you for this. Lord Asheron should be able to learn much from it, to help counter Geraine's mad schemes
You have completed the task I have set before you. Now, it is time for you to gain access to the Paths.

%n touches your brow, and you feel a great upwelling of light and heat fill your entire form. Just when it feels like you may burst from the pressure inside you, the feeling fades down to a comfortable warmth.
Welcome into the Light. You now may gain inner Luminance from your adventures, if they be truly challenging to your strength.
This Luminance, in turn, may be used to empower both auras and items for your benefit.
You may always come to me, for the Path of the Yalain is open to all who have proven themselves to the Light.
In addition, you may also seek out one of the more... specialized... paths from the history of the Empyrean.
You must choose only one specialty path, for when you choose to walk one Path, you lose access to the others.
This book will explain the details.
OracleLuminanceRewardsAccess_1110
OracleLuminanceRewardsQuestStart_1110
I see that you have not yet chosen to walk one of the more specialized paths yet.
There are special benefits that can be gained by choosing to follow one of the Seers of the past cultures of the Empyrean.

The Seer of the Light Falatacot, the Shade of Lady Adja, can be found in the Cathedral of Ithaenc. Her specialties focus on furthering your resistance to damage, and your skill at the skills you have specialized in.

The Seer of the Dark Falatacot, Ka'hiri, can be found near the town of Sawato. Her specialties focus on furthering your ability to damage others, and your skill at the skills you have specialized in..
The Seer of the Dericost, Liam of Gelid, can be found in the entrance of Frore. His specialties focus on furthering your ability to damage others, and your ability to critically damage others.
The Seer of the Haebrean, Lord Tyragar, can be found in Silyun. His specialties focus on furthering your resistance to damage, and your resistance to critical damage.

As for myself, I will empower any and all who have proven themselves and absorbed the Luminance necessary to empower themselves or items to help them. I recommend also following one of the other, more specialized paths.
If you wish to leave one specialty path for another, speak with the Seer you wish to follow, and they will tell you what they require in order to induct you onto their Path.
Be warned, To change one's Path, once chosen, will disrupt your existing attunements to the Light. All of your specialty path auras will fade.
You may empower another Blank Augmentation Gem again in %tqt.
You cannot spend any more Luminance on skill credits.
AvailableLuminance_1000000
You have already gained access to the Paths of the Empyrean, and may earn Luminance. I have no other reward to offer you for this.
OracleLuminanceRewardsQuestStart_1110
OraclePortalEntry
Greetings, I am Nalicana, the Seer of the Yalain.

Due to several factors, including both the return of the... altered... Empyreans, as well as Geraine's manipulations of time via the Book of Eibhil, the Light has empowered several Seers, including myself.
We may, in turn, empower those who prove their worth to walk the ancient Empyrean Paths, and gain power from the Light itself, known as Luminance.

The different eras of Empyrean history have each empowered a Path, from our beginnings in the Paths of the Falatacot, through the more recent Dericost and Haebrean Paths, up to the Path of the Yalain.

To prove your worth, and be empowered to gain Luminance, my task for you is fairly straightforward. There is an Undead, known as Battle Lord Gregor. He is one of Geraine's top nobles, and is the overseer of the forces which now include the beings called Gurog.

Hidden deep in the area held by these Gurog, he organizes the forces Geraine has chosen to put forth. Find him, defeat him, and bring me his Mnemosyne. Contained therein, we hope to find much knowledge on what Geraine is up to.
The Gurog have emerged in an area of the mountains of Northern Osteth. You'll find the Battle Lord deep in the caves there.
